data.title: Icelandic football league system
data.meta_description: The Icelandic football league system is a series of interconnected leagues for club football in Iceland. As of 2013 a fifth level was added to the previous men's format of four levels. As of 2019 there are 79 participating men's teams and 27 women's teams in the football league.
data.text: The Icelandic football league system is a series of interconnected leagues for club football in Iceland.[1] As of 2013 a fifth level was added to the previous men's format of four levels.[2] As of 2019 there are 79 participating men's teams and 27 women's teams in the football league.
